'''''Riddle of the Sphinx''''' is a vertically-scrolling [[action-adventure game]] written by Bob Smith<ref name=giantlist/> for the [[Atari 2600]] and published by [[Imagic]] in 1982. The player, as the Prince of Egypt, must collect treasures and gain strength to release the land from a vile curse.<ref name="SG"/>

Smith wrote several other games for Imagic, including ''[[Star Voyager (Atari 2600)|Star Voyager]]'' and ''[[Dragonfire (video game)|Dragonfire]]''.<ref name=giantlist/>

==Gameplay==
The goal of ''Riddle of the Sphinx'' is to reach the Temple of Ra and make the correct offering.<ref name="manual">{{cite web |title=Riddle of the Sphinx Manual |url=https://archive.org/details/Riddle_of_the_Sphinx_1982_Imagic |website=archive.org |publisher=Imagic |date=1982}}</ref>

==Reception==
